Package io.github.jdbctemplatemapper.core

Class QueryMerge<T>

java.lang.Object
io.github.jdbctemplatemapper.core.QueryMerge<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
IQueryMergeExecute<T>, IQueryMergeFluent<T>, IQueryMergeHasMany<T>, IQueryMergeHasOne<T>, IQueryMergeJoinColumnManySide<T>, IQueryMergeJoinColumnTypeSide<T>, IQueryMergeOrderBy<T>, IQueryMergePopulateProperty<T>, IQueryMergeThroughJoinColumns<T>, IQueryMergeThroughJoinTable<T>, IQueryMergeType<T>
public class QueryMerge<T> extends Object implements IQueryMergeFluent<T>
QueryMerge allows query results to be merged with results of another query. Generally used when multiple relationships need to be populated. 

 See Querying relationships for more info
Author:
ajoseph

    • joinColumnTypeSide

      public IQueryMergeJoinColumnTypeSide<T> joinColumnTypeSide(String joinColumnTypeSide)
      Join column for hasOne relationship. The join column (the foreign key) is on the table of the type model. Example: Order hasOne Customer. The join column(foreign key) will be on the table order (of the type model). The join column should not have a table prefix.
      Specified by:

    • orderBy

      public IQueryMergeOrderBy<T> orderBy(String orderBy)
      The orderBy clause for QueryMerge. For QueryMerge orderBy is only supported for hasMany and hasMany through. orderBy columns have to be on the table of the hasMany/hasMany through side. For hasOne orderBy does not makes sense because the order will be dictated by the mergeList argument in the execute method.
      Specified by:

    • execute

      public void execute(JdbcTemplateMapper jdbcTemplateMapper, List<T> mergeList)
      The query executes an sql 'IN' clause to get the related side (hasOne, hasMany, hasMany through) objects and merges those with the objects in the mergeList. 
       If the the mergeList size is larger than 100, multiple 'IN' queries will be issued with each query
 having up to 100 IN clause parameters to get the records.
      Specified by:
      execute in interface IQueryMergeExecute<T>
      Specified by:
      execute in interface IQueryMergeOrderBy<T>
      Specified by:
      execute in interface IQueryMergePopulateProperty<T>
      Parameters:
      jdbcTemplateMapper - the jdbcTemplateMapper
      mergeList - a list of objects of type.
